theorem Topology.P3_closed_iff_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    Topology.P3 (X := X) A ↔ IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hP3
    -- From `P3` and `hA_closed`, obtain `A ⊆ interior A`.
    have h_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (A : Set X) := by
      simpa [hA_closed.closure_eq] using hP3
    -- Together with `interior_subset`, this yields equality.
    have h_eq : interior (A : Set X) = A :=
      Set.Subset.antisymm interior_subset h_subset
    -- The interior is open, hence `A` is open.
    have h_open : IsOpen (interior (A : Set X)) := isOpen_interior
    simpa [h_eq] using h_open
  · intro hA_open
    exact Topology.isOpen_P3 (X := X) (A := A) hA_open

theorem Nat.factorial_le_pow (n : ℕ) : n! ≤ n ^ n := by
  induction n with
  | zero =>
      simp
  | succ n ih =>
      -- First, upgrade the induction hypothesis to a bound with a larger base.
      have h₁ : n! ≤ (n.succ) ^ n := by
        have hpow : n ^ n ≤ (n.succ) ^ n :=
          Nat.pow_le_pow_of_le_left (Nat.le_succ n) n
        exact ih.trans hpow
      -- Multiply both sides by `n.succ` to prepare for rewriting with `factorial_succ`.
      have h₂ : (n.succ) * n! ≤ (n.succ) * (n.succ) ^ n :=
        Nat.mul_le_mul_left (n.succ) h₁
      -- Rewrite factorial and power, then conclude.
      simpa [Nat.factorial_succ, pow_succ, mul_comm] using h₂

theorem Topology.interior_closure_mono {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hAB : A ⊆ B) :
    interior (closure A) ⊆ interior (closure B) := by
  exact interior_mono (closure_mono hAB)
